\pard\sa280\fs44 \b Independent Advocacy Services\b0\par
\pard\sa240\fs30 \i Who can speak up for you \u8212? independent of DYAR\i0\par
\pard\sa240\fs36 \b What is an advocate?\b0\par
\pard\sa180\fs22\qc \i [IMAGE: Cartoon person standing beside another, supportively pointing forward]\i0\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 An advocate is someone who:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa100\fs28 \bullet  Listens to what you want\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa100\fs28 \bullet  Helps you say what you want\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa100\fs28 \bullet  Helps you understand information\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa100\fs28 \bullet  Speaks up FOR you when you cannot\par
\pard\sa240\fs36 \b Advocates are independent + FREE\b0\par
\pard\sa180\fs22\qc \i [IMAGE: Two separate buildings with a person walking between them \u8212? independence]\i0\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Advocates do NOT work for DYAR.\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 They can speak up for you \u8212? even AGAINST DYAR if needed.\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 All listed services are FREE.\par
\pard\sa240\fs36 \b WA Advocacy Services\b0\par
\pard\sa200\fs30 \b People With Disabilities WA (PWdWA)\b0\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Phone: (08) 9485 8900   Free call: 1800 193 331\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Email: info@pwdwa.org   Web: pwdwa.org\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Best for: All people with disability in WA\par
\pard\sa200\fs30 \b Developmental Disability WA (DDWA)\b0\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Phone: (08) 9420 7230   Web: ddwa.org.au\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Best for: Intellectual / developmental disability + families\par
